Data generation function

Source: R/datagen.R
datagen.Rd

This function generates the simulation data (exposure X, outcome Y, and potential mediators M).

For each subject i = 1, ..., n:

  • \(X_i ~ i.i.d Bernoulli(p = 0.5)\)

  • \(M_{i,k} = \alpha_k X_i + e_{1_{i,k}}\), where \(e_{1_{i,k}} ~ i.i.d N(0, 1), k = 1, ..., K\)

  • \(Y_i = X_i + \sum_k b_{k} M_{i,k} + e_{2_{i}}\), where \(e_{2_{i}} ~ i.i.d. N(0, 1)\)

The 6th-10th M variables (M6,M7,M8,M9,M10) are set to be the true mediators (i.e., having non-zero alpha and beta coefficients).

Specifically, the first 10 coefficients of alpha are set to take some non-zero value a, the 6th to 15th coefficients of beta are set to take some non-zero value b, and all other alpha and beta coefficients are set to be 0.

datagen(n, K, a, b)

Arguments

n

sample size

K

number of potential mediators

a

effect size for X-M path (i.e., non-zero alpha coefficient)

b

effect size for M-Y path (i.e., non-zero beta coefficient)

Value

The resulting dataset has 3 lists: X, Y and M

Examples

datagen(n = 100, K = 50, a = 0.5, b = 0.3)
